         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Cityringen — Transportation System Works — Addendum: Branch off to Sydhavnen</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="45234123"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="WORKS"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The contract comprises the Transportation System (“TS”) for the extension of Cityringen to Sydhavnen, below here Railway Infrastructure and Operation and Maintenance (“O&amp;M”) supplies.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45234111"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45234116"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45234123"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="DK011"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The contract comprises the Transportation System (“TS”) for the extension of Cityringen to Sydhavnen. Metroselskabet (“MS”) is constructing Cityringen in Copenhagen. Cityringen comprises 16 km tunnels, 17 underground stations and 4 shafts. MS is going to construct a branch off to Sydhavnen (“Sydhavnsmetroen”). Sydhavnsmetroen is a dual track branching off the Cityringen, starting after a bifurcation chamber at Havneholmen shaft near the Control and Maintenance Center for Cityringen. Sydhavnsmetroen will be located below ground comprising 5 stations. The TS contract for the extension to Sydhavnen comprises:</P>
                  <P>1) Railway Infrastructure:</P>
                  <P>— Automatic Train Control,</P>
                  <P>— Platform Screen Door System,</P>
                  <P>— Passenger Security and Information System,</P>
                  <P>— Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition (“SCADA”),</P>
                  <P>— Control Centre,</P>
                  <P>— Transmission System,</P>
                  <P>— Radio Communication System,</P>
                  <P>— Intrusion Detection and Access Control Systems.</P>
                  <P>2) Operation &amp; Maintenance (“O&amp;M”) supplies.</P>
                  <P>The TS contract for the extension to Sydhavnen will be an addendum to the original TS and O&amp;M contract regarding Cityringen between MS and Ansaldo STS SpA.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_25_EU>
               <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                  <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                     <D_TECHNICAL/>
                  </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>For technical reasons and due to protection of exclusive rights the works and services covered by the Transportation System (“TS”) contract for the extension of Cityringen to Sydhavnen can only be provided by the excisting TS and O&amp;M supplier on Cityringen, Ansaldo STS SpA.</P>
                     <P>The TS of Sydhavnsmetroen has to be integrated with the TS of the entire Cityringen which consists of a number of TS subsystems. In order to obtain the necessary safety approvals of the entire Cityringen TS and to ensure safe operation of Cityringen it is necessary to make use of the same technologies and systems which have already been chosen for Cityringen. These technoligies and systems are designed and developed specifically for Cityringen by Ansaldo STS SpA and are consequently protected by Ansaldo STS SpA's exclusive rights (IP rights). Therefore the works covered by the contract can only be executed by the excisting TS and O&amp;M supplier on Cityringen, Ansaldo STS SpA.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_25_EU>
